"title": "4639: dung and manure",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4639: dung and manure",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Human dung is considered unclean</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:12-Deut23:14\">DEU 23:12–23:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:12-Ezek4:14\">EZK 4:12–4:14</a></p>\n<h3>The Dung Gate of Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:13\">NEH 2:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:13-Neh3:14\">NEH 3:13–3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:31\">NEH 12:31</a></p>\n<h2>Uses of manure</h2>\n<h3>As fertiliser</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:8\">LUK 13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:35\">LUK 14:35</a></p>\n<h3>As fuel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek4:15\">EZK 4:15</a></p>\n<h2>Symbolic references to dung</h2>\n<h3>As fuel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:10\">1KI 14:10</a></p>\n<h3>As something perishable</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:7\">JOB 20:7</a></p>\n<h3>As something trampled down</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:10\">ISA 25:10</a></p>\n<h3>As something worthless</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:8\">PHP 3:8</a></p>",
